cs.AR, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.ET, cs.DC

This paper discusses the design of QoS routing algorithms for Networks-on-Chip (NoCs) that integrate heterogeneous components and support real-time and latency-sensitive applications. This topic falls under the broad category of Computer Science and Networking (cs.NI) and specifically addresses the sub-categories of Architecture (cs.AR) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) as it deals with the design and control of NoCs. The use of reconfigurable FPGA and NoCs also suggests the sub-categories of Embedded Systems (cs.ET) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
